{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_011gfhjTefEEtiXCiSBBDTPT","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# configctl\n2\t\n3\tA command-line tool for parsing, validating, and converting configuration files across TOML, YAML, and JSON formats.\n4\t\n5\t## Workspace Layout\n6\t\n7\tThis is a Cargo workspace with two crates:\n8\t\n9\t- **`crates/config-core`** — Shared library providing format detection, parsing, and schema validation for configuration files.\n10\t- **`crates/configctl`** — CLI binary that exposes the library's capabilities as user-facing commands.\n11\t\n12\t## Usage\n13\t\n14\t```sh\n15\t# Validate a config file\n16\tconfigctl validate config.toml\n17\t\n18\t# Validate against a schema\n19\tconfigctl validate config.yaml --schema schema.json\n20\t\n21\t# Convert between formats\n22\tconfigctl convert config.toml --output-format json\n23\t```\n24\t\n25\t## Development\n26\t\n27\t```sh\n28\tcargo build            # Build all crates\n29\tcargo test             # Run all tests\n30\tcargo clippy           # Lint\n31\tcargo fmt --check      # Check formatting\n32\t```\n33\t\n34\t## License\n35\t\n36\tMIT\n37\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80e7d795-b855-4bf0-a1e9-fa4a6df7fb25","uuid":"270a9a33-a44c-4c75-b453-5003eb1a9a64","timestamp":"2026-06-23T14:49:35.737Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/private/var/folders/38/_z2xr8rn0m33jpdp5jkbmd500000gn/T/agent-eval/2026-06-23-opus/cases/case-005-rust-monorepo/README.md","content":"# configctl\n\nA command-line tool for parsing, validating, and converting configuration files across TOML, YAML, and JSON formats.\n\n## Workspace Layout\n\nThis is a Cargo workspace with two crates:\n\n- **`crates/config-core`** — Shared library providing format detection, parsing, and schema validation for configuration files.\n- **`crates/configctl`** — CLI binary that exposes the library's capabilities as user-facing commands.\n\n## Usage\n\n```sh\n# Validate a config file\nconfigctl validate config.toml\n\n# Validate against a schema\nconfigctl validate config.yaml --schema schema.json\n\n# Convert between formats\nconfigctl convert config.toml --output-format json\n```\n\n## Development\n\n```sh\ncargo build            # Build all crates\ncargo test             # Run all tests\ncargo clippy           # Lint\ncargo fmt --check      # Check formatting\n```\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37}}}
